      "writtenOn": "2026-04-10T13:20:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, i looked again in section `9.6.13 Links`\n\nand it makes a clear distinction between `subordinate reference property` and `associated reference property` and where they go in a response.\n\nI will try to keep this in mind for future patches 👍\n\n\u003e If you need help, I\u0027m always available on discord to help you 1:1,\n\nappreciate it 💯\n\n\n\u003e  Please let me know if you\u0027re seeing a passing result with this, if so it\u0027s a test bug.\n\nYes, if we put\n```\n\"LogServices\": {\n    \"@odata.id\": \"/redfish/v1/Managers/bmc/LogServices\"\n},\n```\nthen RSV gets an almost clean run `Summary - PASS: 6613, WARN: 357, FAIL: 2, NOT TESTED: 7504` (the 2 fails are unrelated)\n\nI ran with up-to-date RSV and following command\n\n```\n/tmp/rsv-venv/bin/rf_service_validator --auth Session \\\n-i https://s5549-bmc-a0423f63b4a5.lab.9e.network:443 -u root -p *******\n```\n\nthe \u0027LogServices\u0027 property is marked PASS on `/redfish/v1/Systems/Tyan_S5549_Baseboard` response.\n```\nLogServices\n[Link to: /redfish/v1/Managers/bmc/LogServices]\n        PASS\n```\n\nAgree it\u0027s a good idea to let the validator check for bugs like this, would be nice if you can poke them.",
